<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="74" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/494.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Amapala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-24"><hi rend="italic">April 24,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reports that the treaty of peace and amity which has been signed is
                            similar to the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> treaty, and includes
                            provision for a Central American Peace Congress in Nicaragua and a
                            special commercial treaty between the two Republics. Adds that the
                            friendly mediation of the United States is gratefully acknowledged by
                            both countries.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>